1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:05,500
As we continue to expand our understanding of data types and data structures in Python,

2

00:00:05,500  -->  00:00:08,545
we've now arrived in the world of tuples.

3

00:00:08,545  -->  00:00:12,440
Imagine you've decided to go on a cross country road trip and want to

4

00:00:12,440  -->  00:00:16,780
keep track of the fixed geographic coordinates of each place you visit,

5

00:00:16,780  -->  00:00:19,400
knowing that these coordinates will never change.

6

00:00:19,400  -->  00:00:23,610
You wouldn't want these numbers to be altered along the way.

7

00:00:23,610  -->  00:00:26,660
Those coordinates would never change.

8

00:00:26,660  -->  00:00:30,460
This is where tuples come in very handy as a data type,

9

00:00:30,460  -->  00:00:33,800
and we wouldn't want to leave for our trip without them.

10

00:00:33,800  -->  00:00:37,600
Tuples are a data collection type in Python that are immutable,

11

00:00:37,600  -->  00:00:41,000
which is just a fancy word that means once they're created,

12

00:00:41,000  -->  00:00:42,960
they can't be modified or edited.

13

00:00:42,960  -->  00:00:47,060
Tuples are perfect for storing data that should remain constant,

14

00:00:47,060  -->  00:00:50,940
permanent, fixed, and stand the test of time.
